cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper focuses on compressing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method involves quantifying feature map importance and conducting kernel clustering, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the method on image datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
